Sun Hung Kai, China Overseas Land: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-11T00:32:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/sun-hung-kai-china-overseas-land-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 0.5 percent to 24,396.07. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, was little changed at 13,652.92.  Auto-related companies: China’s passenger-car sales to
dealerships in March rose 6.52 percent from a year earlier to
1.3 million units, the China Association of Automobile
Manufacturers said. The nation’s total vehicle sales rose 5.4
percent to 1.8 million units, according to the center.  Geely Automobile Holdings Ltd. (175)  (175 HK), a unit of the
Chinese automaker that owns Volvo Cars, gained 0.3 percent to
HK$3.02. Dongfeng Motor Group Co. (489 HK), Chinese partner of
Nissan Motor Co., gained 2.2 percent to HK$13.02.  Hong Kong developers: Hong Kong home prices fell 0.44
percent in the seven days ended April 3 from a week earlier,
according to Centaline Property Agency Ltd.  Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd. (16)  (16 HK), the world’s biggest
developer, gained 0.7 percent to HK$128.20. Henderson Land
Development Co. (12 HK), the builder controlled by billionaire
Lee Shau-kee, climbed 0.8 percent to HK$56.45.  Aluminum Corp. of China Ltd. (2600 HK): The company and
 Sweden ’s Sapa AB signed an agreement to form a 50-50 venture
that will build an aluminum extrusion plant in western China,
Xinhua News Agency said. Aluminum Corp. of China, known as
Chalco, declined 0.3 percent to HK$7.66.  China Overseas Land & Investment Ltd. (688)  (688 HK): The
developer’s property sales in March rose 13 percent from a year
earlier to HK$7.8 billion ($1 million), according to an e-mailed
statement. China Overseas, controlled by the nation’s
construction ministry, increased 1.8 percent to HK$16.60.  Weichai Power Co. (2338 HK): The company said its unit
Shaanxi Fast Gear Co. will invest 255 million yuan ($39 million)
for a 51 percent stake in a transmission venture with
Caterpillar China Investment Co. Weichai rose 1.8 percent to
HK$54.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Tokyo  at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
